		{
			"id": 124333,
			"karma": -1,
			"text": "First of all, I understand that firefox-40.0-3.fc21 is already obsoleted by\nfirefox-40.0-4.fc21, which sets \"layers.offmainthreadcomposition.enabled\" to\n\"false\" by default. This is a good thing: I experienced not just crashes but\nalso severe problems with screen refresh during scrolling, with lines of text on\nweb pages like https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1253086 temporarily\ndisappearing or with the scrolling on https://admin.fedoraproject.org/updates/\ngetting \"stuck\" when trying to scroll back to the top, unless the mouse pointer\nhovered over the tab bar forcing repaint. Disabling OMTC works around this very\nannoying issue as well.",
			"timestamp": "2015-08-14 14:56:26",
			"update_id": 16759,
			"user": {
				"avatar": "https://seccdn.libravatar.org/avatar/e94867258d359e2d7a1245dc93e9064a702618429791370b5185b58bdf9c5954?s=24&d=retro",
				"email": "bugzilla.i.sekler@mailbox.org",
				"groups": [
					{}
				],
				"id": 1634,
				"name": "isv",
				"openid": "isv.id.fedoraproject.org"
			},
			"user_id": 1634
		},
		{
			"id": 124334,
			"text": "isv: so you experience same stuff that people with gtk3 build (f22)? Are you\nfine with firefox-40.0-4.fc21 now?",
